text: Coffeeville is a town in Clarke County, Alabama, United States. At the 2020 census, the population was 263. The town was incorporated in 1817. == Geography == Coffeeville is located at 31°45'40.543" North, 88°5'20.940" West (31.761262, -88.089150), on high ground on the east side of the Tombigbee River.
